  "id": "g11",
  "title": "Claude Code Project Structure: Workspace Blueprints",
  "category": "Architecture",
  "readTime": "5 min read",
  "summary": "A modern, production-ready AI coding workspace layout optimized for autonomous CLI agents.",
  "content": "### \ud83c\udf32 Claude Code Project Structure\n\n<div className=\"flex justify-center my-6\">\n  <img src=\"/assets/digest/4.jpeg\" className=\"rounded-2xl border border-white/10 shadow-xl max-w-full h-auto mx-auto\" alt=\"Claude Code Project Structure\" />\n</div>\n\nA modern, production-ready AI coding workspace blueprint. Learn how to configure your project tree and harness hook events to build safe, autonomous development environments.\n\n---\n\n### \ud83d\udee0\ufe0f Key Architectural Elements\n\n#### 1. CLAUDE.md Essentials\nContains your tech stack, architecture overview, testing constraints, and styling guides. Keep it under 500 lines to avoid context bloat.\n\n#### 2. Hooks and Middleware\n- **PreToolUse:** Block or validate parameters *before* a tool executes (e.g., check database queries or payment amounts).\n- **PostToolUse:** Inspect or clean tool output *before* feeding it back to Claude.\n- **PreCommit / Secret Scanning:** Intercept commits to verify no secrets are leaked.\n\n#### 3. Context Management\n- **0-50% Context:** Work freely.\n- **50-70% Context:** Monitor token usage.\n- **70-90% Context:** Run `/compact` to summarize history.\n- **90%+ Context:** Run `/clear` to start fresh."
